      <para styleclass="Heading1">Mechanism | Add Trace-Point</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Add Trace-Point</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Terminology:</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:104px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box-Elements" style="text-align:right;">Trace-Point : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Trace-Point</text> shows the locus of a moving <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> for one machine-cycle on the <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Plane</text> of the active <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Trace-Point" anchor="DragaTrace-Point">Special Conditions</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> to drag the </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Add Trace-Point</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Trace-Point</text> does <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">NOT</text> add a <text styleclass="Element">Point</text> to the model. You must select a <text styleclass="Element">Point</text> that is in the model.</para>
