        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Notes">Notes: </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">To add a </text><text styleclass="Element">Trace-Point</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> of a </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">relative</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> to a </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Part</text> (that is,<text styleclass="Element">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Interface2" style="color:#ff0000;">NOT</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">relative</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text>), you should add a <text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">To add the Point to a Part</para>
          <list id="8" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Edit a </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> to add a </text><text styleclass="Element">Circle</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Part, </text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">and </text><text styleclass="Element">Profile</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Circle</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Do </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add 2D-Cam</text></para>
          <list id="8" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Select the </text><text styleclass="Interface">centre-Point</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Circle</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> (see 1</text><text styleclass="VariableName">) </text></li>
            <li styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Select the </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> in which you want to show the </text><text styleclass="Element">Trace-Point</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">To show the </text><text styleclass="Element" style="font-style:italic;">Trace-Point</text></para>
          <list id="8" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Edit the </text><text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> (see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-2DCam" styleclass="Element">2D-Cam dialog-box</link><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">) and show only the </text><text styleclass="Parameter">Pitch-Circle</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> as the </text><text styleclass="Element">Trace-Point</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">.</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><anchor id="DragaTrace-Point"><keywords><keyword>Trace-Point<keyword>How to drag a TracePoint.</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor>Special Condition</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-style:normal;">You can </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;">drag</text><text style="font-style:normal;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;">if ALL</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> of these conditions are met:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-style:normal; color:#ff0000;">IF</text><text styleclass="BodyText BI" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="BodyText BI" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">In the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor</text><text styleclass="BodyText BI" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">:</text></para>
          <list id="9" type="ol" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <list id="9" level="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#49;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
              <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">To add the Point, you do: </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Part-Editor &gt; Add Point</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text><br/><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">The </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets"> cannot be a </text><text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">, </text><text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">, or </text><text styleclass="Interface">center-Point.</text></li>
            </list>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT2"><text style="font-style:normal; color:#ff0000;">AND IF</text></para>
          <list id="9" level="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#49;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:normal;">You do </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-style:normal; color:#ff0000;">not</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:normal;"> add a dimension or a constraint to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-style:normal; color:#ff0000;">AND IF</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:normal;"> in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:normal;">:</text></para>
          <list id="9" level="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#49;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:normal;">You add a </text><text styleclass="Element">Trace-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:normal;"> to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Notes">Note:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">To drag the <text styleclass="Element">Point</text> more easily:</para>
          <list id="10" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px;">Reduce the <text styleclass="Parameter">Number-of-Steps</text> to ~30 in the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Edit-MachineSettings">Machine Setting dialog-box</link>&#32;</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT2">and / or</para>
          <list id="10" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px;"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Drag the </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> and then </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">keep the mouse-pointer very still</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> until the </text><text styleclass="Element">Trace-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> moves.</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
